      • getLogger

        public static Logger getLogger(java.lang.String fullNameWitoutRoot)
        Returns a Logger with the given full name. This method implicitly adds the root Logger's name to the provided name. The provided name should omit the name of the root Logger. If the requested Logger does not exist, it will be created.
        Parameters:
        fullNameWitoutRoot - The name of the Logger to return.
        Returns:
        The Logger with the requested full name.
        See Also:
        Logger.getFullNameWithoutRoot()
